was really very odd — at the same time she got rather on my nerves — I mean the things she said. I was losing my grip somehow. I shook myself mentally as she returned.

'Now you've done it,' she said. 'Helene is not at home.'

'Tant mieux,'

I replied, 'she's probably on her way here, and really you ought to understand how terribly impatient I am to see her.'

